MooPlaceholder
--------

MooPlaceholder is a simple MooTools wrapper for text input elements (input and textarea) to support a placeholder feature.

Usage:

HTML:
<input type="text" class="placeholder" value="some initial value that will act as a placeholder" />

or

<input type="text" class="placeholder" data-placeholder="some initial value that will act as a placeholder" />
...

<script type="text/javascript" src="mooplaceholder.js"></script>

JavaScript:
window.addEvent('domready',function() {
  Placeholder.listen();
});

CSS:
input.focus {
  //details for when the input element is focussed upon
}

input.blur {
  //details for when the element is not active
}
